    <string name="ECDHHelpTitle" translatable="false">Elliptic Curves Diffie Hellman</string>
    <string name="ECDHHelpText">
        Given:\n
        Curve E: y²=x³ + a*x + b mod p\n
        Public Point P (x,y)\n\n
        Alice chooses KprivA between 2 and #E-1 and Bob chooses KprivB between 2 and #E-1\n\n
        Alice calculates KpubA = KprivA*P and Bob calculates KpubB = KprivB*P\n\n
        KpubA and KpubB are exchanged over the network\n\n
        Alice calculates KAB = KprivA * KpubB and Bob calculates KAB = KprivB * KpubA
    </string>


