    <string name="ECDSAHelpTitle" translatable="false">Elliptic Curves Digital Signature Algorithm</string>
    <string name="ECDSAHelpText">
        Given:\n
        Curve E: y²=x³ + a*x + b mod p\n
        Generator A (x,y) with ord(A)\n\n
        SETUP:\n
        Choose private number d between 0 and ord(A)\n
        Calculate public Point B = d*A\n
        Choose Ephemeral Key kE between 0 and ord(A)\n
        Choose message x to sign\n
        Public Key = (E , A , B)\n\n
        SIGNING:\n
        Calculate R = kE * A\n
        Set r = X-Coordinate of R\n
        Calculate s = (x + d*r) * kE⁻¹ mod q\n
        Signature = x, (r , s)\n\n
        VERIFICATION:\n
        Calculate w = s⁻¹ mod q\n
        Calculate u1 = w * x mod q\n
        Calculate u2 = w * r mod q\n
        Calculate P = u1 * A + u2 * B\n\n
        Is X-coordinate of P = r ?\n
        If yes, signature is vaild\n
        else signature is invalid\n
    </string>

